<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Menace" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Menace,</orth> vb. to threaten; absol.: <cit><quote>who ever knew the heavens m. so?</quote> <bibl n="shak. jc 1.3.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 3, 44</bibl></cit>. trans.: <cit><quote>m. me,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.175" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 175</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.183" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 183</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.133" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 3, 133</bibl>. <cit><quote>to whom by oath he --d revenge upon the cardinal,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 1.2.137" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 2, 137</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>